This paper discusses the use of mmwave frequencies and massive MIMO for wireless communications systems, which falls under the categories of information theory (cs.IT), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), systems and control (cs.SY), architecture (cs.AR), and multimedia (cs.MM). The focus on reducing cost and power consumption through signal processing and antenna techniques suggests a strong emphasis on implementation and practical considerations, which further supports the likelihood of these categories.
